ery module is designed to fit back into the same `[error, value]` shape."},"300":{"id":"/docs/guides/quickstart-23","page_id":"/docs/guides/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/guides/quickstart#step-1-stop-throwing-for-routine-failures","content":"When a tuple flow grows past one branch, use `yieldless/result` to keep it readable."},"301":{"id":"/docs/guides/quickstart-24","page_id":"/docs/guides/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/guides/quickstart#step-1-stop-throwing-for-routine-failures","content":"Keep this modest. If one `if (error)` branch is clearer, use the branch."},"302":{"id":"/docs/guides/quickstart-25","page_id":"/docs/guides/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/guides/quickstart#step-2-group-related-work-under-one-cancellation-signal","content":"`runTaskGroup()` gives you a shared abort signal and sibling failure propagation."},"303":{"id":"/docs/guides/quickstart-26","page_id":"/docs/guides/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/guides/quickstart#step-2-group-related-work-under-one-cancellation-signal","content":"If `readRefs()` throws, the group aborts the shared signal, waits for `readStatus()` to settle, and then rethrows the original failure.\nIf the request or UI flow already has an `AbortSignal`, pass it in so the whole group inherits upstream cancellation."},"304":{"id":"/docs/guides/quickstart-27","page_id":"/docs/guides/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/guides/quickstart#step-2-group-related-work-under-one-cancellation-signal","content":"When the work is a list rather than a few named tasks, use `mapLimit()` to keep pressure on the outside world under control."},"305":{"id":"/docs/guides/quickstart-28","page_id":"/docs/guides/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/guides/quickstart#step-2-group-related-work-under-one-cancellation-signal","content":"The result order matches the input order, and the first tuple error aborts the remaining in-flight work."},"306":{"id":"/do