k#why-this-is-friendlier","content":"A parent `AbortSignal` can cancel the whole batch when the user navigates away."},"345":{"id":"/docs/recipes/bounded-batch-work-10","page_id":"/docs/recipes/bounded-batch-work","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/recipes/bounded-batch-work#why-this-is-friendlier","content":"`concurrency` is explicit, so expensive work stays polite by default."},"346":{"id":"/docs/recipes/bounded-batch-work-11","page_id":"/docs/recipes/bounded-batch-work","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/recipes/bounded-batch-work#good-variation-stream-the-input","content":"If repositories come from an async source, use `yieldless/iterable` instead of building a large array first."},"347":{"id":"/docs/recipes/bounded-batch-work-12","page_id":"/docs/recipes/bounded-batch-work","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/recipes/bounded-batch-work#avoid-unbounded-fan-out","content":"That can launch dozens or hundreds of subprocesses. Use `mapLimit()` or `mapAsyncLimit()` so the user’s machine stays responsive."},"348":{"id":"/docs/recipes/checkout-flow","page_id":"/docs/recipes/checkout-flow","type":"page","content":"Checkout Flow","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Recipes","Recipes"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/recipes/checkout-flow"},"349":{"id":"/docs/recipes/checkout-flow-0","page_id":"/docs/recipes/checkout-flow","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/recipes/checkout-flow","content":"A customer checkout example with validation, inventory reads, payment resilience, rate limits, and receipt jobs."},"350":{"id":"/docs/recipes/checkout-flow-1","page_id":"/docs/recipes/checkout-flow","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/recipes/checkout-flow#the-moving-parts","content":"The moving parts"},"351":{"id":"/docs/recipes/checkout-flow-2","page_id":"/docs/recipes/checkout-flow","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/recipes/checkout-flow#checkout-service","content":"Checkout service"},"352":{"id":"/docs/recipes/checkout-flow-3","page_id":"/docs/recipes/checkout-flow","type":"heading","ta